  "response": "Hoei Shin was a Buddhist monk from China who is claimed to have traveled to the Americas, specifically to Mexico, around 499 AD. According to some historical accounts, he made this journey nearly a thousand years before Christopher Columbus. His story is part of a collection of narratives that suggest pre-Columbian trans-oceanic contact between Asia and the Americas. However, the historical evidence supporting Hoei Shin's journey is sparse and largely considered to be speculative or mythical by many historians and scholars.",
